4 CONC te, Germany&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;Death: Jan 19 1738 - Kleinfischlingen, Landau, Palatinate, Bavaria, Germany&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;Burial: Jan 19 1738 - Kleinfischlingen, Landau, Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany&
4 CONC amp;lt;br&amp;gt;Father: &lt;a&gt;Stein&lt;/a&gt;&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;Husband: &lt;a&gt;Johann Wendel Georg Traut&lt;/a&gt;&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;Children: &lt;a&gt;Anna Katherina Traut&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a&gt;Ha
4 CONC ns George Trout&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a&gt;Hans Nicholas Traut&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a&gt;Hans Michael Traut&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a&gt;Anna Margaretha Traut&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a&gt;Johann Deobalt Traut&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a&gt;Ma
4 CONC ria Elisabetha Racke (born Traut)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a&gt;Anna Barbara Traut&lt;/a&gt;&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Additional information: &lt;br&gt; &lt;br&gt;LifeSketch: Maria Appolina Stein (c
4 CONC . 1691-1738) was born approximately 1691, most likely in Kleinfischlingen (near Landau), Electoral Palatinate, Holy Roman Empire (now in Südliche Weinstraße, Rheinland-Pfalz, Germany). Maria&#039;s 
4 CONC maiden name was most likely &quot;STEIN,&quot; and the suffix of &quot;LIN&quot; simply indicated she was an unmarried young maiden, as was the Palatine naming convention of the times. Her presumptive
4 CONC  birth date of 1691 is accepted by most researchers, but Maria &quot;may&quot; have been born as late as about 1702.

In about 1722, Maria married Johann Wendel Georg TRAUT (farmer, age 32) presumably
4 CONC  at Kirche St. Margaret (&quot;Church of St. Margaret&quot;), the Evangelisch-Lutherisch church in Kleinfischlingen. &quot;Kirche St. Margaret,&quot; most often simply referred to as the &quot;Protest
4 CONC antische Pfarrkirche&quot; (&quot;Protestant Parish Church&quot;), dates from before 1400, although the ancient steeple was extended in the 1700s, with the protestant rectory being added in 1748, abou
4 CONC t 10 years after Wendel TRAUT&#039;s departure. &quot;Kirche St. Margaret&quot; is located at Schulstraße 4 (#4 Schul Street), about a ½ block north of Hauptstraße (&quot;Main Street&quot;). Its Ca
4 CONC tholic counterpart, &quot;Katholische Kirche St. Simon und Judas&quot; is located at Hauptstraße 37 (#37 Main Street), with the Protestant church grounds nearly adjoining the rear of the Catholic chu
4 CONC rch grounds. Wendel and Maria would not have known the &quot;Katholische Kirche St. Simon und Judas,&quot; since it was not erected until 1770, some 32 years after Maria&#039;s death and Wendel&#039;s
4 CONC  departure for the New World.

(8) Children were born to this union.

Sadly, Maria Appolonia [STEINLIN] TRAUT died 19 Jan 1738, four days after giving birth to daughter Anna Barbara TRAUT in Kleinfisc
4 CONC hlingen. Maria is presumably buried in the &quot;Protestantische Pfarrkirche&quot; (&quot;Protestant Parish Church&quot;) cemetery in Kleinfischlingen, although a marker is no longer known to be evide
4 CONC nt. Research continues...

