1 NOTE Wendel Trout, II 
Birth: Oct. 29, 1743
Lancaster County
Pennsylvania, USA
Death: Aug. 31, 1820
York County
Pennsylvania, USA
Husband of Elizabet DRUKENBROD (1765-1825)
Wendel TROUT II, the twin of Ann
2 CONC a Maria Magadalena TRAUT, was born 29 Oct 1743 in Strasburg Twp (now Pardise Twp), Lancaster, PA, the son of the immigrant, Johann Wendel Georg TRAUT (1689-1760) and second wife Maria Magdalena WALTER
2 CONC  (1717-1760). At least eleven children were born to this union. 
Wendell was a soldier in the Revolutionary War. He volunteered as a Private in 1780 in Captain William Smith's Co. (ref. Pennsylvania A
2 CONC rchives 5th series, vol. 7). He also served in Captain Alexander Whites Co., 1st Battalion of Lancaster County, Commanded by Col. George Stewart. (PA Archives, 5th series, vol. 7, page 97).
In 1787, W
2 CONC endel and his family moved from Lancaster County, PA to "Hopewell Center" York County, Pennsylvania. From Genealogical Reports for York County, PA., in the Historical Society, vol. 9, page 76, we read
2 CONC ; "Wendel Trout and wife Elizabeth Trout emigrated to York County, PA., May 20, 1787. Purchased land of David Kennedy of Hopewell and wife Mary; to Wintle Trout late of Lancaster County, yeoman, for 4
2 CONC 10 £ species 152.154 acres in Hopewell.
The first of Wendell and Elizabeth Trout's children were Baptized in the Brickerville Lutheran Church, Lancaster County, PA. After the family had moved to York
2 CONC  County, they evidently attended the [St. John] Sadler's Lutheran Church as that is where the balance of their children were Baptized. It is believed that Wendell and Elizabeth are buried in the oldes
2 CONC t section of the cemetery adjacent to the church, but no stone marks the graves. Many old stones were discarded when the cemetery was cleaned and revised in the late 1920's or early 1930's.
Source: Ba
2 CONC sed on research by the late V. Kyle Trout (1919-1999), lightly edited for clarity
- - -
Also see the Memorial (cenotaph) erected in memory of Wendel TROUT II and wife Elizabet at the site of their far
2 CONC m in Hopewell Center established in 1787.
--- Research by Craig H. Trout

