Johann Paul TRAUT was born 26 November 1739 in Strasburg (now paradis
2 CONC e) Township, Lancaster, PA, the son of Johann Wendel Georg TRAUT (1689-1760) and Maria Magdalena WALTER (1717-1760).

Paul married Anna Maria SCHAEFFER on 6 April 1762 in Lancaster, Lancaster, PA. At 
2 CONC least nine children were born to this union.

Johann Paul TRAUT was a Revolutionary War soldier Who Served in the Lancaster County Militia from 1777 through 1786, and perhaps longer.

--- Research by 
2 CONC Craig H. Trout
 
 
