22 Dec 1773 - Paul Trout, yeoman, of Strasburg Twp, Lancaster, PA, purchases for the consideration of 100 pounds lawful money of Pennsylvania a series of three separate tracts from William Lig
2 CONC git and wife Catherine, and John Liggit, all being of Strasburg Twp.  The first tract consisted of 65 acres situated ìon the Barren Hill dividing Strasburg and Sadsburyî townships; the second tract 
