1 NOTE <p style="text-align: left;" dir="ltr"><br />Mrs. Mary Terry Goodwin Kuyk.<br />DAR ID Number: 159650 <br /><br />Descendant of Robert Goodwin, Stephen Terry, Ensign Michael Trout, John Pendleton, Cap
2 CONC t. Augustine Leftwich and Capt. Charles Yancey, as follows: <br />1. Thompson W. Goodwin (b. 1864) m. 1897 Martha Leftwich Terry (b. 1867). <br />2. Edmund Pendleton Goodwin (1830-69) m. 1852 Lucy Ann
2 CONC  Chiles (1834-1906); Peyton Leftwich Terry (1834-98) m. 1857 Mary Susan Trout (1839-1910). <br />3. William Thompson Goodwin (1807-33) m. 1830 Elizabeth Kimbrough Pendleton (1813-30); Stephen Terry (1
2 CONC 807-57) m. 1828 Lucinda Leftwich (1810-48); John Trout (b. 1813) m. Eliza Shaver. <br />4. John Chapman Goodwin (1779-1845) m. 1803 Anna Rhodes Thompson (1783-1865); William Terry (1777-1815) m. Patie
2 CONC nce Martha Farmer; George Trout (1782-1850) m. Mary Miller; Edmund Pendleton (1787-1838) m. 1808 Unity Yancey Kimbrough (1787-1866); Peyton Leftwich (1769-1859) m. 1793 Mildred Fuqua. <br />[p.208] 5.
2 CONC  Robert Goodwin m. 1766 Jane Tulloch; Stephen Terry m. Sarah Fuqua; Michael Trout m. Elizabeth Baer; Henry Pendleton (1762-1822) m. 1786 Alcey Ann Winston (b. 1769); Augustine Leftwich m. 1765 Mary Tu
2 CONC rner; Joseph Kimbrough m. Elizabeth Yancey. <br />6. John Pendleton m. 1760 Sarah Madison; Charles Yancey m. Mary Crawford. <br />Stephen Terry, a patriot, assisted in collecting and driving cattle to
2 CONC  the camp in Pittsylvania County, Va., 1781. He was born in Halifax County; died, 1797, in Pittsylvania County, Va. <br />Michael Trout served as ensign, 1776, in the Augusta County, Virginia militia.
2 CONC  He was born in Augusta County; died in Rockingham County, Va. <br />John Pendleton (1719-99) was too old for active service; but, in 1775, was appointed by a convention of delegates at Richmond, to s
2 CONC ign part of the large issue of Treasury notes. He was born and died in Caroline County, Va. <br />Augustine Leftwich (1744-80) received a pension for service as captain in the Virginia troops. He was 
2 CONC born in Caroline County; died in Bedford County, Va. <br />Charles Yancey (1741-1841) commanded a company of Louisa County, Virginia militia. He was born and died in Louisa County, Va.&nbsp;</p>
