1 NOTE <p><div>29 March 1851&nbsp; James was born at 22 Thomas Street, Waterloo Road, Lambeth</div></p><p><div>1851 census&nbsp; James was only one day old.</div></p><p><div>Later that year James was taken t
2 CONC o the Great Exhibition according to his obituary.</div></p><p><div>1861 census&nbsp; age 10, living at 1 Poole's Lane, Chelsea. Pool Lane is still there - redeveloped into townhouses.</div></p><p><div
2 CONC >1871 census&nbsp; age 20. Still at Pool Lane&nbsp;</div></p><p><div>2nd June 1873 age 22, living 10 Schofield Terrace, Fulham, (one of a row of houses built by his father) Iron Founder (from marriage
2 CONC  certificate). Marriage to Louisa Croughton of 5 Schofield Terrace, in a double ceremony along with James's sister Rebecca marrying Walter Featherstone at St James' Church, Moor Park Road, Fulham.</di
2 CONC v></p><p><div>His children were:</div><div>Fanny Kershaw Schofield, James Henry Schofield, Frederick Charles Schofield, Susan Victoria Schofield, John Kershaw Schofield, Albert Benjamin Schofield and 
2 CONC Herbert WalterSchofield.</div></p><p><div>1873-1876 At some point between these dates he joined the Great Northern Railway.</div></p><p><div>1876 Living at Wharf Pinxton, Derbyshire (birth certificate
2 CONC  of eldest child, Fanny Kershaw Schofield.)</div><div>1878 Living at Barnet, Hertfordshire (birth certificate of second child James Henry Schofield)</div></p><p><div>1879 Living at Hale Magna, Lincoln
2 CONC shire, (birth certificate of third child, Frederick Charles Schofield)</div></p><p><div>1881 census &nbsp; Cannot trace him aqnywhere - was he on a night train?</div></p><p><div>1882&nbsp; living Grea
2 CONC t Northern Road, Dunstable</div></p><p><div>1891 census living Great Northern Road, Dunstable, age 40, Clerk on Great Northern Railway.</div></p><p><div>1898 living 2 Theodore Road, Lewisham Commercia
2 CONC l Clerk (from father's will, codicil dated 1898 appoints him executor)</div></p><p><div>1901 census&nbsp; Great Northern Road, Dunstable, age 50, Florist</div></p><p><div>1908 Under his father's will 
2 CONC he inherited the following properties:</div></p><p><div>622 King's Road, leasehold house, shops and stables occupied by Mr Priddle, greengrocer;</div></p><p><div>644 King's Road, leasehold house, shop
2 CONC s and stables occupied byMr Audin</div></p><p><div>2 Schofield Place, Sands End Lane, freehold</div></p><p><div>2 Rose Cottages</div></p><p><div>53 Farm Lane, Walham Green, freehold occupied by Mrs Ed
2 CONC wards</div></p><p><div>70 Farm Lane, Freehold shops and workshops occupied by Mr Bristow</div></p><p><div>Three Cups Coffee Tavern- half rent and profit of leasehold.</div></p><p><div>&nbsp;</div></p>
2 CONC <p><div><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>  <o:DocumentProperties>   <o:Version>14.00</o:Version>  </o:DocumentProperties>  <o:OfficeDocumentSettings>   <o:AllowPNG/>  </o:OfficeDocumentSettings> </xml><![endif
