1 EVEN He was an ardent Liberal, vigourously supporting Sir Charles Dilke MP for Fulham and Chelsea. He was a Fulham vestryman and Guardian of the Poor which entailed supervising maintenance in the Fulham Workhouse. He built many house in Britannia Road, Fulham and surrounding streets and a terrace of five houses in King's Road, Fulham still known as Schofield Terrace but also 620-628 King's Road. The family lived in the terrace.
