1 NOTE !He is said to have been born at Kleinfi<p>!He is said to have been born at Kleinfischlingen, Rheinland Pfalz, Germany. This was in the wine country of Landau.  The church book of the Evangelical Luth
2 CONC eran Church, Kleinfischlingen, Rheinland-Pfaltz records the birth of his children. !They sailed on the ship "Winter Galley" from Rotterdam about the first of July and arrived in Philadelphia 5 Sep 173
2 CONC 8 with 252 passengers.  Some of his friends and neighbors from the Landau area also came to America on the same ship.  They were:  Johann Jacob Stahl age 25, Johan Michael Romer age 18, Melichor Stall
2 CONC  age 16, Johann Peter Hoffmasn age 27, Georg Hoffman age 37, Adam Hoffman age 18, Johan Melichor Weiss age 20 and Johannes Lingenfeldter. They arrived in Philadelphia on 5 Sep 1738 from Rotterdam via 
2 CONC Deal, England !11 May 1737 Wendel bought 161 1/2 acres of land 4 miles east of the borough of Strasburg adjoining Daniel Flerre's land (who was also from Landau).  When he died he willed it to his old
2 CONC est son of his second marriage, Johan Paul Traut. !On 23 Jan 1739 he married as his second wife, Maria Magdolina Walter, in Strasburg, Lancaster Co., PA. !In Feb 1760, Wendel wrote his will in which h
2 CONC e left 1/3 to his wife Magdolina, the "Old place", 27 acre tract and the 10 acre field to his son, Paul, and 30 pounds each to his four younger daughters.  His son Wendel to get 50 pounds.  Of his chi
2 CONC ldren by his first wife, George and Nicholas" already had been portioned off" except Nicholas' four boys:  Jacob, Michael, Henry and Valentine.  Each to receive 1 pound and 5 shillings.  Daughter Mary
2 CONC  to receive 8 pounds and son Michael--5. !The name was Americanized to "Trout' about 1860 when Wendel Traut died.  Strasburg Twp. was split in 1843.  The eastern part became Paradise Twp which is wher
2 CONC e the Trouts lived. !The Old Dutch or Betelhans Lutheran Church  was later called St Michael's Evangelical Lutheran Church of Strasburg, PA was located about 1 1/2 miles SE of the borough of Strasburg
2 CONC .  The date of the first record was 5 Jan 1 754.  Records of St Michaels began in 1753 and continued until 1757.  The records from that time until 1775 are missing.</p>
