2 CONC  lists 48 phones for Traut.</p><p></p><p>Strasburg Township during this person's lifetime is Paradise Township in 2009.</p><p></p><p>In 1738 immigrated from home in Kleinfischlingen to Philadelphia, P
2 CONC ennsylvania on ship Winter Gally out of Rotterdam via Deal, England.  Arrived 5 September 1738.  Signed the Oath of Allegiance to England.  Various editiions of the ship's passenger list show him as W
2 CONC endel Drauth and Wintell Draut (D.N. 2530) and as Wintell Draut and Wenell Trauth (D.N. 2531).  Information about that ship and sailing to America are in D.N. 2532.  Information about ships' passenger
2 CONC  lists is in D.N. 2533.</p><p></p><p>Buried in the Trout Burial Ground (grave stone no longer evident in 2009)</p><p></p><p>Craig Trout doubts that J.W.G.T.'s father was Hans Velton Traut, as commonly
2 CONC  claimed, because of DNA non-matches (D.N. 2534).  His detailed research notes and conclusive DNA findings are in D.N. 2659.</p><p></p><p>If J.W.G.T. is H.V.T.'s son, then a pedigree to about 1545 is 
2 CONC in D.N. 2525 at page 4.</p><p></p><p>Kati Hill's family tree lists descendants of Johann Wendel Traut (D.N. 2612).  Since her data is less reliable than Craig Trout's (D.N. 2528, 2529) her data should
2 CONC  be entered only after his.</p><p></p><p>In September 2009 Ancestry.com had 1,333 trees that included John Traut.  They should be searched only after Craig Trout's data (D.N. 2528, 2529) has been ente
2 CONC red.</p><p></p><p>Craig Trout's detailed and extensive notes for this person are in my separate Traut data base.</p>
