1 NOTE bio from Geo. E. Trout: 250 years of my Trout family <p>INTRO-During the ongoing research into our Trout families, it became evident that much interesting history was being lost in the ...charts... CH
2 CONC APTER ONE IN EUROPE BEFORE EMIGRATION Early in the spring of the year 1738, a 49-year-old farmer in the town of Kleinfischlingen in the wine country of Landau in the Rheinland Pfalz was preparing for 
2 CONC a long journey to America. (The two villages of Kleinfischlingen and Grossfishlingen were adjacent ... the prefix "klein" indicates little and "gross" means big. "Fischlingen" indicates fish.) This fa
2 CONC rmer's name was Johann Wendel George TRAUT who was married to Margaretha Mock on 24 April 1672. Her father was Wendell MOCK, an attorney of Anwalt. It is believed his grandfather was Hans Leonhardt TR
2 CONC AUT who was Burgomeister [ principal magistrate, comparable to a mayor, of a city or town in the Netherlands, Flanders, Austria, or Germany.] in Impflingen in 1645, 1651 and 1652. His first wife's nam
2 CONC e was Agnes, who died before 1666; then he married Elizabeth KOCH on 20 February 1666. At that time the "Palatinate" was ruled by a Pfalzgraf or Count Palatine, one of the nine electors of the Holy Ro
2 CONC man Emperor, thus the Kurpflaz or Electoral Palatinate. The capitol was moved form Heldelbert of Mannheim in 1720. During the 30-years-war (1618-1648) there was no ruler. Many places in the Electoral 
2 CONC Palatinate were so badly destroyed by the plundering armies of Austria, Bavaria, France, Lorraine, Spain and Sweden that they had to be almost totally rebuilt. In fact, it has been ...</p>
