1 NOTE Life sketch<p>Wendel Trout, II </p><p>Birth: Oct. 29, 1743</p><p>Lancaster County</p><p>Pennsylvania, USA</p><p>Death: Aug. 31, 1820</p><p>York County</p><p>Pennsylvania, USA</p><p>Husband of Elizabet
2 CONC  DRUKENBROD (1765-1825)</p><p>Wendel TROUT II, the twin of Anna Maria Magadalena TRAUT, was born 29 Oct 1743 in Strasburg Twp (now Pardise Twp), Lancaster, PA, the son of the immigrant, Johann Wendel 
2 CONC Georg TRAUT (1689-1760) and second wife Maria Magdalena WALTER (1717-1760). At least eleven children were born to this union. </p><p>Wendell was a soldier in the Revolutionary War. He volunteered as a
2 CONC  Private in 1780 in Captain William Smith's Co. (ref. Pennsylvania Archives 5th series, vol. 7). He also served in Captain Alexander Whites Co., 1st Battalion of Lancaster County, Commanded by Col. Ge
2 CONC orge Stewart. (PA Archives, 5th series, vol. 7, page 97).</p><p>In 1787, Wendel and his family moved from Lancaster County, PA to "Hopewell Center" York County, Pennsylvania. From Genealogical Reports
2 CONC  for York County, PA., in the Historical Society, vol. 9, page 76, we read; "Wendel Trout and wife Elizabeth Trout emigrated to York County, PA., May 20, 1787. Purchased land of David Kennedy of Hopew
2 CONC ell and wife Mary; to Wintle Trout late of Lancaster County, yeoman, for 410 £ species 152.154 acres in Hopewell.</p><p>The first of Wendell and Elizabeth Trout's children were Baptized in the Bricke
2 CONC rville Lutheran Church, Lancaster County, PA. After the family had moved to York County, they evidently attended the [St. John] Sadler's Lutheran Church as that is where the balance of their children 
2 CONC were Baptized. It is believed that Wendell and Elizabeth are buried in the oldest section of the cemetery adjacent to the church, but no stone marks the graves. Many old stones were discarded when the
2 CONC  cemetery was cleaned and revised in the late 1920's or early 1930's.</p><p>Source: Based on research by the late V. Kyle Trout (1919-1999), lightly edited for clarity</p><p>- - -</p><p>Also see the M
2 CONC emorial (cenotaph) erected in memory of Wendel TROUT II and wife Elizabet at the site of their farm in Hopewell Center established in 1787.</p><p>--- Research by Craig H. Trout</p><p></p><p>Family lin
2 CONC ks: </p><p>Parents:</p><p>Johann Wendel Georg Traut (1689 - 1760)</p><p>Maria Magdelena Walter Traut (1717 - 1761)</p><p>Spouse:</p><p>Elizabet Drukenbrod Trout (1765 - 1825)</p><p>Children:</p><p>Jos
