1 NOTE <p>On 21 September 1751, three brothers and a sister came to America on the ship, Two Brothers, from Rotterdam via Cowes. Only Johan George Etsler`s name appears on the ship`s list of passengers. It c
2 CONC ould have been the father with the same name or the son (believed to be the eldest) since he would have been old enough to be listed. Also appearing on the ship`s list is a Johan Jacob RATGE/RADGE who
2 CONC  is likely the husband of the sister or perhaps the father-in-law. Later church records show children to a Margaret and Jacob Radge/Ratge, but since the ages are unknown, this could be them or possibl
2 CONC y one of their children. The will of the sibling Johannes does indicate his sister was married to a Radge. Thus far, the parents of these siblings are unknown. Other spellings of this surname have bee
2 CONC n AETZLER, UTZLER. - Dorinda Davis Shepley</p> <p>www.MidMdRoots.com</p>
1 NOTE <p>a Johann George Etzler took oath, ship Two Brothers, Mstr Thomas Arnot, from Rotterdam on Sep 21, 1751 [PA Oaths of Allegience]</p><p><p></p></p><p><p> Will dtd Feb 8, 1813 lists the following chil
2 CONC dren:</p></p><p><p></p></p><p><p>   sons, George, Andrew, Jacob, Michael</p></p><p><p>   daughters, Catherine married William Young, deceased</p></p><p><p>                     Mary Gloria married Jaco
2 CONC b Barnitz</p></p><p><p>                     Elizabeth married Rev Henry Heiner (on Jul 14, 1808)</p></p><p><p></p></p><p><p>Information for the old Etzler generations compiled by:</p></p><p><p>   Dr W
2 CONC ilbur Devilbiss      (rec'd before 1990)</p></p><p><p>   Brooklawn Apts, # 203</p></p><p><p>   Frederick, MD  21701</p></p><p>   301-662-0583</p>
