1 NOTE <p>[117340.ftw]</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Robert Means ran away from home when he was 18 because his father had forbidden him to marry a poor girl in County Tyrone.  He arrived in Philadelphia in 1784 and we
2 CONC nt to live with an uncle, Isaac Means, on the south branch of the Potomac, near Moorefield, Virginia in Hampshire County.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>He married Jane Neely and had two sons and two daughters be
2 CONC fore Jane's death.</p> From the notes of Connie Street.
