1 NOTE <p><span style="font-size: 13px; background-color: #dcd0cf;">Served in the Civil War as a Private in Co E, 4th Michigan V.I., 4th Brigade, 3rd Div, 14th AC. Fought at Murfreesboro. His father, Frederi
2 CONC ck Sweigart Rhoades, fought in the War of 1812.</span><br style="font-size: 13px; background-color: #dcd0cf;" /><br style="font-size: 13px; background-color: #dcd0cf;" /><span style="font-size: 13px; 
2 CONC background-color: #dcd0cf;">Samuel "fell off" a train outside Carlin, Nevada on his way back to Stanton from Healdsburg, California, where he was visiting his sister, Sarah Rhoades Kniss Farrar. The f
2 CONC amily's version says that he was robbed, beaten and pushed off the train as he was found carrying only some material he had in his jacket which he had purchased to make a dress for one of his daughter
2 CONC s.</span></p>
