1 NOTE <p>When Jacob's will was probated in 1854 it stated that there were 3 sons and 4 daughters living.  I could not account for the last two daughters. The 1840 census shows one son under 5 and 1 girl and
2 CONC  1 boy both between 10 and 15.  I have no idea who they are. The 1850 census showed the other 2 girls and 3 boys.  The assumption is that the two missing girls were born after the 1850 census and befo
2 CONC re the death of Jacob in 1854.  Copy of will is in documentation.  Everything to Sarah.  Executor was brother Sam.</p><p><p></p></p><p><p>There is also a son Oliver but no record can be found, perhaps
2 CONC  it is the second name of either Cornelius or Jacob.</p></p><p><p></p></p><p><p>York County Historical Society..Nagle file..Jacob 3190 will.</p></p><p>RIN: MH:N200</p>
