1 NOTE <p>[227038.ged]</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>RFN: 16</p><p>The Clary family originated in ancient Donegal, Ireland.</p><p>Thomas Taylo r patented fifty acres of land for bringing John Clary to</p><p>the colonie
2 CONC s in 1677 .  John was 17 years old at the time that he</p><p>arrived in America. [Broderbund W FT Vol. 1, Ed. 1, Tree #2466, Date of</p><p>import: 08/08/1996]</p><p>" John Clary, Sr. w as born in 1660
2 CONC  in England.  He reached Maryland in</p><p>October 1677.  He was one of 39 persons transported by Captain Thomas</p><p>Taylor.  Little was known of John Clary in Maryland.  His port of</p><p>arrival w
2 CONC as either St. Marys or Annapolis--the only towns in the</p><p>colony at the time.  After working several years to repay t ravel costs</p><p>he would have then received 50 acres of his own and engaged 
2 CONC in</p><p>fa rming. He was the father of four children : John clary, Jr., William</p><p>Clary, An n Clary, Daniel Clary."  [by James H. Sharpe, Jr. of</p><p>Hiddenite, NC - his sourc es are family memb
2 CONC ers, census records and</p><p>Ralph Shearer Rowland & Star Wilson Rowland, Clary Genealogy - Four</p>Early American Lines and Related Families.]
